				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I mean, it's &quot;11&quot; bits because there's a &quot;redundant&quot; 3-bit latch in PPU2 for each horizontal scroll register. Keeping track of D2 on the first write so that it can be transfered later. It's there to make the API not suck.<br /><br />Total number of latches is apparently<br />13 bits per horizontal scroll: seven coarse, three fine, and three for a 1-deep FIFO for fine scroll<br />10 bits per vertical scroll<br />eight bits shared across all eight registers in PPU1 as a 1-deep FIFO</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

